# Document workflow

## Ownership

| Content | Home | This repo keeps |
|---------|------|-----------------|
| Cross-repo ADR/ARC | [devdocs](../../devdocs/) | stub redirect only |
| Platform ops | devdocs/ops | — |
| Domain glossary | [devdocs/glossary.md](../../devdocs/glossary.md) | [docs/agents/domain.md](docs/agents/domain.md) |
| Canopy API / worker behavior | `docs/` | full doc |
| Canopy implementation plans | `docs/plans/` | full doc |

## Layout

- `docs/arc/` — repo-local implementation arcs
- `docs/adr/` — repo-local ADRs
- `docs/plans/plan-NNNN-*.md` — implementation plans
- `docs/agents/` — on-demand agent indexes

## Numbering

Sequential zero-padded NNNN per prefix under `docs/**` (including
`docs/plans/archived/`). Increment from highest existing number.

## Structure

YAML-style header: **Status** (DRAFT | ACCEPTED | SUPERSEDED), **Date**,
**Related** links.

## Agent pull policy

Read [docs/plans/README.md](docs/plans/README.md) first. Do not bulk-read
`docs/plans/archived/` unless a task cites a specific plan id.

## Cross-referencing

Use markdown links. Example from `docs/plans/`:
[ADR-0001](../adr/adr-0001-encoding-one-per-artifact.md).

Platform docs: relative `../../devdocs/adr/…` or GitHub URLs when cloned alone.

## Cursor plans → `docs/plans/`

After a Cursor-built plan (`.cursor/plans/*.plan.md`), persist to
`docs/plans/` — merge into parent numbered plan when work extends it,
otherwise create next `plan-NNNN-short-slug.md`. Drop Cursor-only scaffolding;
default **DRAFT**.
